The paper discusses the use of deep learning systems for animal re-identification using camera trap data, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The methodology involves similarity learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions biases and inconsistencies in human analysis, which could be addressed through computer security (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
